result.execSummary:
The defendant Robert J Cummings Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Robert J Cummings Jr is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Robert J Cummings Jr was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Robert J Cummings in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Robert J Cummings in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant to enter plea to Ct 2 in 15CF47 & Ct 2 in 15CF54.  State will move to dismiss Cts 1 & 3 in 15CF47 and Ct 1 in 15CF54.  Will request a PSI in 15CF47 and request jail in 15CF54.  Atty Gumz agrees.  
Defendant enters No Contest plea to Ct 2 in 15CF47 and Ct 2 in 15CF54.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  C  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct 2 in 15CF47 and Ct 2 in 15CF54.  Court will dismiss Cts 1 & 3 in 15CF4 and Ct 1 in 15CF54.
Counsel make sentencing statements.
BY THE COURT:  Court sentences defendant to serve 7 months in the Marquette County Jail, consecutive to any sentence he is now serving.  *Granted huber.  *Granted 158 days credit.  *Sentence deemed served.  *Pay costs of $243.00.  *Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge of $200.00.  
Payments on costs to be held until he is released from jail.

Defendant Robert J Cummings in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Robert J Cummings in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
15CF47 & 15CF54 tracking together:
  Atty Gumz states that the Defendant received a copy of the information in both matters & waives the reading.  Atty Gumz enters a Not Guilty plea for both matters.
Atty Gumz states that an offer has been provided and treatment court has been looked into.  Atty Gumz asks for this to be set out a couple weeks to see what route the defense will be taking.

BY THE COURT: Not Guilty pleas entered in both matters.
Set for return.
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for January 21, 2016 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Robert J Cummings in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Robert J Cummings in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
15CF54 & 15CF47:
  Atty Hendee states that in speaking with Atty Gumz; the defendant will be waiving the Prelim today.  Atty Gumz agrees and has discussed the waiver with his client.  Atty Gumz states that the defendant would be looking into treatment court and would like an Arraignment date set.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees with the waiver.  Court accepts the waiver of the Prelim.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it.  Case bound over for trial or further proceedings.

Atty Hendee files the information in both cases with the court.   Atty Gumz states that the Defendant received a copy of the information in both cases & waives it's reading.
Set for Arraignment.
bond continued.  Arraignment scheduled for December 17, 2015 at 10:45 am.
Notice of Motion & Motion to Dismiss

with conditions:
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance
*Not to go on the premises of any place that sells alcohol as its primary business
*Submit to random breath tests as requested by Law Enforcement

Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.
Court questions the defendant regarding the time limits for the Preliminary Hearing.  Defendant waives time limits for the Prelim.

BY THE COURT:  Time limits waived; set Preliminary Hearing.

Defendant Robert J Cummings in court, in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee requests a $2,500 cash bond with conditions.
Court questions the defendant.
Defendant makes a statement to the court and states that he cannot come up with that much cash.

BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $1,500 Cash bond with conditions:
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance
*Not to go on the premises of any place that sells alcohol as its primary business
*Submit to random breath tests as requested by Law Enforcement  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 16, 2015 at 10:00 am.
